    "message": "Add system snapshot support with Snapper on Btrfs\n\nImplements snapshot functionality for system stability as requested in issue #8.\n\nFeatures:\n- Automatic pre/post snapshots on package updates (snap-pac)\n- Hourly timeline snapshots with automatic cleanup\n- Bootable snapshots via GRUB menu (grub-btrfs)\n- Helper scripts: snapshot-create, snapshot-list, snapshot-diff,\n  snapshot-delete, snapshot-rollback\n\nThe setup gracefully handles non-Btrfs filesystems by skipping\nsnapshot configuration and informing the user.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
    "parents": [{ "sha": "e9714e45234d2fa7626a573db05851e3e5bd010a", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/eg0rmaffin/vapor-rice-i3/git/commits/e9714e45234d2fa7626a573db05851e3e5bd010a", "html_url": "https://github.com/eg0rmaffin/vapor-rice-i3/commit/e9714e45234d2fa7626a573db05851e3e5bd010a" }],
